headline: Lennar Misses Earnings Estimates. The Stock Is Dropping.
summary: Lennar  one of the nation’s largest home builders, missed earnings estimates for its fourth quarter and issued disappointing guidance, sending shares falling in after-hours trading.  Lennar earned $1.93 a share, or $2.03 a share, excluding mark-to-market gains on technology investments, and a $156 million one-time loss on an exchange offer linked to its land development spinoff, on $9.4 billion in revenue in its fourth quarter.  “Even as interest rates moved slightly lower in our fourth quarter, the overall market remained challenged,” Lennar co-CEO Stuart Miller said in a statement.
